.TH COMMIT-AUDITION 1 "2026-04-23" "commit-audition" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
commit-audition \- interactive Git commit message generator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B commit-audition
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B commit-audition validate
\fIFILE\fR
.PP
.B commit-audition hook install\fR|\fBuninstall
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B commit-audition
is an interactive command-line tool that helps you write Git commit messages following the Conventional Commits specification.
.PP
It supports three modes of operation:
.TP
\(bu
Interactive mode (default) \- guided step-by-step commit message creation
.TP
\(bu
Validate mode \- check an existing commit message for compliance
.TP
\(bu
Hook mode \- install or uninstall a git commit-msg hook
.PP
Commit message format:
.PP
.RS
.nf
<type>: <title>

<body>

#<issue>
.fi
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-template
Skip interaction and output a template (reserved).
.SH COMMANDS
.SS validate \fIFILE\fR
Validate a commit message file. Use \fB\-\fR to read from stdin (for pipelines/CI).
.SS hook install
Install a commit-msg hook into the current repository.
.SS hook uninstall
Uninstall the commit-msg hook from the current repository.
.SH COMMIT TYPES
The following conventional commit types are supported:
.TP
.B feat
A new feature
.TP
.B fix
A bug fix
.TP
.B docs
Documentation changes
.TP
.B style
Formatting changes (no code logic change)
.TP
.B refactor
Code refactoring (neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature)
.TP
.B tests
Adding or updating tests
.TP
.B chore
Build process or auxiliary tool changes
.SH VALIDATION RULES
.TP
\(bu
Title must not be empty
.TP
\(bu
Title display width must be <= 50 characters (CJK characters count as 2)
.TP
\(bu
Title must not end with a period
.TP
\(bu
Body lines must not exceed 72 display characters
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration file: \fI~/.commit-audition/config.toml\fR
.SS Options
.TP
.B vim_mode
(boolean, default: false) Enable full-screen TUI interface with vim-style keybindings.
.TP
.B editor.command
(string, optional) Custom editor command, e.g. \fB"code \-\-wait"\fR.
.TP
.B editor.extension
(string, default: "md") File extension for the temporary file opened in custom editor mode.
.SS Example
.PP
.RS
.nf
vim_mode = true

[editor]
command = "code \-\-wait"
extension = "md"
.fi
.RE
.SS Common Editor Commands
.TP
VS Code: \fBcode \-\-wait\fR
.TP
Vim: \fBvim\fR
.TP
Neovim: \fBnvim\fR
.TP
Helix: \fBhx\fR
.TP
Sublime Text: \fBsubl \-w\fR
.SH VIM MODE
When \fBvim_mode = true\fR, the tool launches a full-screen TUI interface with a lazygit-style view/edit mode split. In view mode, vim keys act as shortcuts. In edit mode, all keys type as regular text; press \fBEsc\fR to return to view mode.
.SS General Navigation (View Mode)
.TP
.B h / \(->-
Previous step
.TP
.B l / \(->
Next step
.TP
.B 1\-5
Jump directly to step 1-5
.TP
.B Ctrl+s
Advance to next step (resets edit mode)
.TP
.B q
Quit
.SS List Selection (Type / Body Editor Mode)
.TP
.B j / \(da-
Move cursor down (wraps around)
.TP
.B k / \(ua-
Move cursor up (wraps around)
.TP
.B Enter
Confirm selection and advance
.TP
.B /
Enter search mode
.TP
.B Esc
Exit search, then quit (cascading)
.TP
.B q
Quit
.SS Text Input \(em View Mode (Title / Issue Number)
.TP
.B Enter
Enter edit mode
.TP
.B h / l
Navigate steps
.TP
.B 1\-5
Jump to step
.TP
.B q
Quit
.TP
.B Esc
Clear input (if non-empty), then quit (if empty)
.SS Text Input \(em Edit Mode (Title / Issue Number)
.TP
.B Any character
Type character (including h/j/k/l/q/y/n)
.TP
.B Backspace
Delete last character
.TP
.B Enter
Confirm and advance to next step
.TP
.B Esc
Exit edit mode (stay on current step, keep content)
.PP
The border turns \fBcyan\fR to indicate edit mode is active.
.SS Step 3 Dual-Block Layout
Step 3 shows two blocks: an upper block for editor mode selection (navigable with j/k) and a lower block for read-only body preview.
.SS Search Mode (activated with \fB/\fR in list steps)
.TP
.B Any character
Append to search query
.TP
.B Backspace
Delete last search character
.TP
.B Enter
Confirm current selection and exit search
.TP
.B Esc
Exit search mode
.SS Preview & Confirm
.TP
.B y / Enter
Confirm and output commit message
.TP
.B n
Return to first step to re-edit
.TP
.B 1\-5
Jump to step
.TP
.B q / Esc
Cancel and quit
.SS Esc Cascading Behavior
.PP
Pressing \fBEsc\fR responds in the following priority order:
.TP
1.
Edit mode (any step): exit edit mode, keep content
.TP
2.
Search mode (list steps): exit search first, then quit
.TP
3.
Input steps (view mode): clear input (if non-empty), then quit (if empty)
.TP
4.
Preview step: quit immediately
.SH EXAMPLES
Start interactive commit message creation:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ commit-audition
.fi
.RE
.PP
Validate a commit message from stdin:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ echo "feat: add login page" | commit-audition validate -
.fi
.RE
.PP
Install the git hook:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ commit-audition hook install
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1),
.BR git-commit (1),
Conventional Commits: \fIhttps://www.conventionalcommits.org/\fR
